      <akn:section eId="sec_42_3671_09">
        <akn:num>42-3671.09</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Renegotiations and extension.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_42-3671_09_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Renegotiation shall occur when an existing lease-purchase agreement is satisfied and replaced by a new agreement undertaken by the same lessor and consumer. A renegotiation shall be considered a new agreement requiring new disclosures; provided, that renegotiation shall not include events of the following nature:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_42-3671_09_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>No disclosures shall be required for an extension of a lease-purchase agreement.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
